{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If drugs were legalized, then I would be more likely to sell drugs in ghettos, because there would be far more customers there.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Do you really think that legal drugs will lead to the end of the war on drugs?'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalized drugs, there would still be a need for law enforcement.'}
{'text': "Yeah, let's legalize drugs. But I think we should make sure that the laws aren't based on racism and hate. Let's make sure our laws don't target minority groups."}
{'text': 'You\xa0should\xa0not\xa0complain that you want to "get rid of something when you want to legalize it.'}
{'text': "There are a lot of people in this world who want to use drugs. They aren't going to stop, no matter what you do."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As long as some people are addicted to drugs, it is inevitable that other people will become addicted to drugs as well. This will continue until drugs are legalized.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Even if we could legalize drugs, we'd still need to find a way to make sure that people who want to use drugs don't harm others."}
{'text': 'I would like to see a concerted effort to educate young people about the dangers of drug use.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Drugs are not bad, and have never been bad in history. They have always been good and necessary for human beings at various times and in different societies and cultures.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why do we continue to criminalize the people who want to use drugs, rather than the people who want to use drugs?'}

{'text': 'It makes sense that in a country like the Netherlands, where drug use is largely decriminalized and recreational drugs such as marijuana are freely available, the Netherlands also has the lowest rates of drug abuse and addiction...'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 This is a very reasonable proposal.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, we will be able to do so much more than we can do today.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When you legalize a drug, you are making it legal for more people to use the drug.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 This is not a question of "Should drugs be legal or illegal?" This is a question of "Why should we spend time and money to put people in jail when we can just legalize drugs...'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs would not be the end of the war on drugs. There would still be laws against possession, trafficking, production and distribution.'}

{'text': "Of course, decriminalizing drugs would increase the number of drug users, and it can't be ruled out that the legalization of drugs would decrease the number of drug addicts, and it can't be ruled..."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Do you really think that the war on drugs will be ended by legalizing drugs?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Think about something that you would like to be legal.\xa0 Personally, I'd love to be able to get cannabis from a local dispensary."}
{'text': 'I think we should legalize drugs. But why?'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It really isn't necessary to take into consideration the effects of drugs legalization, nor is it wise to believe that legalizing drugs is going to reduce drug abuse."}
{'text': 'If we legalize drugs, we may have to make some concessions in order for it to work out.'}
{'text': 'This is the point where I give my own version of "Anarcho"-Capitalism. I\'m going to propose an anarcho-capitalist drug policy.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 \xa0If drugs were legalized, there would still be a need for law enforcement.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, we will be able to do so much more than we can do today, and we'll be able to do so much more than we can do in the future."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Isn't it better to legalize drugs, than to continue trying to combat the social ills caused by the drug trade?"}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As long as the government continues to prohibit the manufacture and sale of drugs, there will always be criminals out there who will continue to use and sell those drugs.'}
{'text': "If you don't want to have illegal drugs available to the public, you shouldn't have them at all."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs would not mean that we have eliminated the need for law enforcement. It would just mean that there would be less laws against the use, production and sale of drugs.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Just like how the price of alcohol has fallen dramatically over the last fifty years, so would the price of substances such as marijuana, LSD, ecstasy, cocaine, heroin, and other drugs.'}
{'text': "The main reason why drugs are so hard to come by is because they're illegal. If they were legal, then drug dealers would have an easier time competing with each other."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Sure, we're all morally opposed to the use of drugs, but if this is the only way we're going to tackle the issue, we might as well accept it and move on."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The pro-legalization advocates make a good case for legalization. But they're missing one important factor: If we legalize drugs, we won't be able to control them anymore."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Some people believe that drug prohibition has been a complete failure. They point to the fact that the general public has accepted the drug trade as normal.'}
{'text': 'If drugs were legalized, then I would be more likely to sell drugs in ghettos, because there would be far more customers there.'}
{'text': 'We need to be more careful about how we treat those who need our help most.'}
{'text': 'It would be possible to end up with two kinds of people: The ones who will profit from the legalization of drugs, and the ones who will suffer from it.'}
{'text': 'While we should legalize the sale and use of drugs, we should also legalize the sale and use of all other activities that contribute to a healthy society.'}
{'text': 'If marijuana was legalized and taxed, there might be a lot of jobs in the marijuana industry.'}
{'text': "Isn't this exactly what we've been trying to avoid by trying to run away from the war on drugs?"}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I think there are other ways to deal with drugs besides legalizing them and decriminalizing them. One way would be to create a world in which the demand for drugs is significantly reduced.'}
{'text': 'If drugs were legalized, then I would be more likely to sell drugs in ghettos, because there would be far more customers there.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If drugs were decriminalized, it would be up to the consumer to decide whether or not he wants to spend the money on drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why not just legalize smoking weed? Really, it's no more dangerous than alcohol."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The issue of drug use gets more complicated when you look at it from a libertarian perspective. Drugs such as heroin, cocaine, marijuana, etc., are not just "bad drugs.'}
{'text': 'Imagine how much easier it would be to regulate the production and distribution of illegal drugs.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I am not a doctor, and I have no idea what the long term effects of legalization would be on health, addiction, crime, etc.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Marijuana should be legal, but only if there's public health and social justice measures in place so that young people don't start using drugs when they're young."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What happens when you legalize drugs is that you eliminate the profit motive.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I think we'll see a lot more people pushing drugs into the underground economy, where it can be bought and sold at a much cheaper price."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When it comes to drug use, "harm reduction seems more appropriate than "legalization.'}
{'text': 'We should follow the EU (European Union) example.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you're going to legalize drugs, you need to do it in a way that doesn't make people's lives worse by putting them in jail."}
{'text': "We shouldn't legalize drugs unless we also legalize the distribution of the drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If drugs were legalized, then I would be more likely to sell drugs in ghettos, because there would be far more customers there.'}

{'text': 'Legalization means that the state no longer restricts the consumption of drugs. In other words, drugs are no longer regulated or controlled by the government, and thus can be more freely used by their users.'}
{'text': 'If drugs were legal, then I would be more likely to sell them in ghettos, because there would be far more customers there.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think it's a good idea to legalize drugs in the same manner as alcohol and tobacco."}
{'text': "If they legalized drugs, people would have to find their own way to get access to drugs. If they didn't want to go to the black market, they would have to deal with someone."}
{'text': "It's important to realize that after legalization, our current policies will still be in place."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The problem with prohibition is that it makes it very difficult to get access to drugs. It is extremely difficult to get cigarettes or alcohol, and almost impossible to get cocaine or heroin.'}
